China said the move was unilaterally initiated by the U.S. and Beijing would &ldquo;react with firm countermeasures&rdquo; if the Trump administration doesn&rsquo;t &ldquo;revoke this erroneous decision.&rdquo; It accused the U.S. of harassing diplomatic staff and intimidating Chinese students, confiscating personal electrical devices and detaining them without cause. Chinese diplomatic missions and personnel also recently received bomb and death threats, it added.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;China strongly condemns such an outrageous and unjustified move which will sabotage China-U.S. relations,&rdquo; the Foreign Ministry said. &ldquo;We urge the U.S. to immediately withdraw its erroneous decision. Otherwise China will make legitimate and necessary reactions.&rdquo;
